/**
 * @mainpage Bowling Mini-Game API Documentation
 *
 * @section intro Introduction
 *
 * Welcome to the Bowling Mini-Game API documentation. This project provides
 * a complete 3D bowling game implementation using Raylib, featuring realistic
 * physics, dynamic camera system, and full scoring mechanics.
 *
 * @section desc Project Description
 *
 * The Bowling Mini-Game is a software implementation of a classic 10-pin bowling
 * game built with Raylib for 3D graphics rendering. The game offers an immersive
 * bowling experience with realistic ball physics, pin collision dynamics, and
 * authentic scoring rules following official bowling regulations.
 *
 * The project is designed as a modular mini-game that can be integrated into
 * a larger multi-game lobby system, featuring an opaque API for clean separation
 * of concerns.
 *
 * @section features Features Implemented
 *
 * @subsection spin Ball Spin Mechanics
 * - Adjustable spin amount using A/D keys
 * - Visual spin indicator showing direction (Left/Right/Straight)
 * - Realistic spin effect on ball trajectory
 * - Spin decay over time during roll
 * - Visual curve preview in aim guide
 *
 * @subsection camera Dynamic Camera System
 * - Smooth camera following during ball roll
 * - Lerp-based camera transitions
 * - Automatic return to default position after roll
 * - Configurable camera offset and lerp speed
 * - Perspective projection with 45-degree FOV
 *
 * @subsection physics Physics Simulation
 * - Ball physics with velocity and friction
 * - Pin collision detection and response
 * - Pin-to-pin collision chain reactions
 * - Tumble physics for fallen pins
 * - Angular velocity and rotation for pins
 * - Gravity simulation for falling pins
 * - Gutter detection and handling
 * - Ball shadow and pin shadow rendering
 *
 * @subsection scoring Full Scoring System
 * - Complete 10-frame bowling rules
 * - Strike detection and bonus calculation
 * - Spare detection and bonus calculation
 * - Special 10th frame rules (bonus rolls)
 * - Cumulative score tracking per frame
 * - Real-time scoreboard display
 * - End-game statistics (strikes, spares, gutters, average)
 *
 * @subsection visuals Visual Effects
 * - Particle system for pin impacts
 * - Aim guide with trajectory preview
 * - Power meter with color-coded levels
 * - Spin meter with direction indicator
 * - Full-screen end game summary
 * - Play Again / Quit buttons
 *
 * @section controls Controls
 *
 * | Action | Control |
 * |--------|---------|
 * | Aim and Throw | Click and drag mouse |
 * | Add Left Spin | A key (hold) |
 * | Add Right Spin | D key (hold) |
 * | Adjust Aim | Left/Right Arrow keys |
 * | Adjust Power | Mouse Scroll Wheel |
 * | Reset Ball | R key |
 * | Skip Reset Timer | SPACE key |
 * | Quit Game | ESC key |
 *
 * @section assets Assets Used
 *
 * The game uses the following texture assets located in the `assets/` directory:
 *
 * | Asset | File | Description |
 * |-------|------|-------------|
 * | Ball Texture | boules.png | Multiple bowling ball designs |
 * | Pin Texture | quille.png | Bowling pin sprite |
 * | Lane Texture | piste.png | Bowling lane surface |
 *
 * @note If textures fail to load, the game falls back to procedural 3D primitives
 *       (spheres for balls, cylinders for pins, planes for lanes).
 *
 * @section api API Overview
 *
 * The bowling game API provides a minimal, opaque interface for integration:
 *
 * - `bowling_initGame()` - Allocate and initialize a new game instance
 * - `bowling_gameLoop()` - Execute one frame of the game (input, logic, render)
 * - `bowling_freeGame()` - Release all resources and cleanup
 *
 * The `BowlingGame_St` structure is opaque to external modules. All interaction
 * occurs through the public API functions defined in bowlingAPI.h.
 *
 * @section structure Project Structure
 *
 * - `include/` - Public header files (bowlingAPI.h, utils/types.h, utils/configs.h)
 * - `src/` - Source files containing the implementation
 * - `assets/` - Texture files for balls, pins, and lane
 * - `docs/` - Doxygen documentation files
 * - `build/` - Compiled objects and binaries
 *
 * @section dependencies Dependencies
 *
 * - Raylib (graphics, input, 3D rendering)
 * - Raymath (vector operations)
 * - Standard C library (stdlib, string, math)
 *
 * @section author Author
 *
 * - **Author:** Maxime CHAUVEAU
 * - **Date:** 2026-02-25
 * - **Version:** 2.0
 *
